Police spokesperson FC Van Wyk said two men aged 34 and 41 came to the event to drop off an “unknown pupil”. As they left the venue they were killed by an unidentified male who fired several shots. Anti-Gang Unit members also made several arrests on the Cape Flats. on Sunday, the AGU members apprehended a 45-year-old man in Kleinvlei and found a 9mm pistol with no ammunition. Van Wyk said in an unrelated incident, members of the Crime Intelligence unit followed up on information of irregularities at premises in Eerste River. Van Wyk said they arrested a member of a gang who was in possession of an illegal firearm. Western Cape Provincial Commissioner Khombinkosi Jula commended the members for the arrest. sisonke.mlamla@inl.co.za Cape Argus